    My teenage son started using this CeraVe Salicylic Acid Cleanser morning and night, usually in the shower because that’s the only time I can get him to actually wash his face properly. He pairs it with Benzagel 5% Acne Gel, and honestly, it’s been working well to keep the typical teenage skin drama under control. Less redness, fewer breakouts, and he doesn’t complain about dryness, which is a win in my books.I like that it’s fragrance free - he already smells like a walking sock most days, so we don’t need any fake scents on top of that. The fact that it’s gentle but still exfoliates is great, especially for his bumpy arms (keratosis pilaris runs in the family). I sneak a pump now and then myself, and it doesn’t strip my skin either.Big bonus: no microbeads, so I’m not feeling guilty rinsing it down the drain.One bottle lasts a while, even with daily teenage overuse.

